WEBVTT

00:20.287 --> 00:23.355
[instrumental music]

00:24.458 --> 00:26.091
[engine revving]

00:26.093 --> 00:27.493
[laughing]

00:27.495 --> 00:30.429
I'm flying!

00:30.431 --> 00:32.430
[chuckling]

00:33.667 --> 00:36.135
Come on, Aunt Sadie!

00:39.306 --> 00:42.374
[giggling]

00:45.179 --> 00:48.714
[Nicole] Catch me! Catch me, Aunt Sadie!

00:50.418 --> 00:52.518
[Nicole screaming]

00:54.188 --> 00:57.256
[giggling]

01:04.598 --> 01:07.299
[music continues]

01:08.235 --> 01:09.835
[giggling]

01:11.639 --> 01:13.105
[tires screeching]

01:13.107 --> 01:15.140
[intense music]

01:15.142 --> 01:17.476
[Sadie] Nicole!

01:17.478 --> 01:20.079
[Nicole screaming]

01:20.081 --> 01:23.082
[intense music]

01:23.084 --> 01:25.284
[engine revving]

01:27.121 --> 01:30.189
[birds chirping]

01:32.626 --> 01:34.126
[Young Nicole] I owe you my life, Aunt...

01:34.128 --> 01:35.461
Sadie.

01:43.170 --> 01:46.238
[instrumental music]

02:15.469 --> 02:18.537
[music continues]

02:35.156 --> 02:36.421
[twig snaps]

02:36.423 --> 02:38.857
[dog barking]

02:41.328 --> 02:43.495
[gasps]

02:43.497 --> 02:44.830
Hey.

02:46.333 --> 02:47.833
What's out there?

02:47.835 --> 02:50.903
[mellow music]

03:23.871 --> 03:26.939
[moaning]

03:29.376 --> 03:32.444
[breathing heavily]

03:33.414 --> 03:35.347
[chuckles]

03:35.349 --> 03:36.782
[sighs] Mm.

03:36.784 --> 03:38.617
Your workout routine's gonna kill me.

03:38.619 --> 03:39.885
Huh.

03:41.255 --> 03:43.288
You are my workout routine.

03:44.658 --> 03:46.458
[Alex] You're not leavin' already, are you?

03:46.460 --> 03:49.928
I do not wanna be here when your daughter gets home from school.

03:49.930 --> 03:52.598
[water running]

03:54.501 --> 03:57.569
[birds chirping]

04:05.546 --> 04:06.912
[car lock beeps]

04:20.961 --> 04:24.696
-Hey, Chloe. -Hello, Derek.

04:25.499 --> 04:27.733
Is my daughter upstairs?

04:38.312 --> 04:40.412
Goddammit, Nicole.

04:45.452 --> 04:48.553
[birds chirping]

04:54.328 --> 04:56.428
[Chloe] So, did you use protection?

05:03.637 --> 05:05.771
I mean, if you can't even talk about it,

05:05.773 --> 05:08.640
maybe you're not ready for sex.

05:14.548 --> 05:17.849
Hey... I'm not making any judgments.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.351
I just don't wanna see you make

05:19.353 --> 05:21.420
the same mistakes that I did when...

05:22.890 --> 05:24.056
You can't wait until after dinner

05:24.058 --> 05:26.091
to remind me I was a mistake?

05:26.093 --> 05:30.595
[chuckles] That is not what I said!

05:30.597 --> 05:31.997
Yeah, that's not the best choice of words.

05:31.999 --> 05:34.733
-I don't think. -No kidding.

05:34.735 --> 05:37.069
Well, I mean, you can't give her ammunition like that.

05:37.071 --> 05:39.037
[sighs] Well, Alex,

05:39.039 --> 05:42.074
she turns everything I say into ammunition.

05:42.076 --> 05:46.345
I bet she's in there right now trash-talking me to Shay.

05:46.347 --> 05:48.513
Trash-texting.

05:48.515 --> 05:51.016
Yeah, Shay's the same way with her mom.

05:52.619 --> 05:54.653
She just pushes me away.

05:54.655 --> 05:57.923
You know, I think you could be talkin' about us.

05:57.925 --> 06:00.726
I mean, you push me away.

06:00.728 --> 06:03.829
Don't you think this is nice, you know, the two of us in bed?

06:03.831 --> 06:06.131
Talking about how our day went.

06:07.668 --> 06:09.935
We should try it in person sometime.

06:09.937 --> 06:12.471
I should probably go check on her.

06:12.473 --> 06:14.506
[Alex on phone] Hey, Chloe...

06:14.508 --> 06:17.709
I like you. Okay?

06:17.711 --> 06:20.946
And more than w-whatever this is.

06:22.483 --> 06:24.082
Goodnight, Alex.

06:25.886 --> 06:28.987
Hello? Oh, shit.

06:31.024 --> 06:33.892
[instrumental music]

06:33.894 --> 06:36.094
[fan squeaking]

06:52.746 --> 06:53.812
[floorboard creaking]

06:53.814 --> 06:56.581
[footsteps approaching]

06:56.583 --> 06:59.418
[Chloe] Nicole? Can we talk?

06:59.420 --> 07:01.052
[Chloe sighs]

07:01.054 --> 07:04.089
[music continues]

07:25.012 --> 07:27.112
[Chloe] I miss her, too.

07:40.160 --> 07:43.228
[indistinct chatter]

07:45.232 --> 07:46.865
[girls giggling]

07:48.035 --> 07:50.869
With those red streaks and the jacket.

07:50.871 --> 07:53.138
Like, where did she get that...

07:53.140 --> 07:54.840
[girls giggling]

07:54.842 --> 07:57.843
[sighs] I think my mom is straight up ignoring me now.

07:57.845 --> 08:00.045
I wish my mom would ignore me.

08:01.915 --> 08:03.882
And the boots.

08:04.852 --> 08:07.919
[indistinct chatter]

08:13.861 --> 08:16.895
Stella, Charlotte and I have a question for you.

08:20.801 --> 08:22.801
[screams]

08:22.803 --> 08:24.236
Damn, Nicole, what'd she do?

08:24.238 --> 08:27.506
[Serena sobbing]

08:29.910 --> 08:32.077
[Serena] Why?

08:32.880 --> 08:34.913
[telephone ringing]

08:36.984 --> 08:39.985
Hello? Yes, this is Chloe.

08:42.890 --> 08:44.289
Thank you.

08:47.861 --> 08:50.929
[instrumental music]

09:00.040 --> 09:01.873
[swing squeaking]

09:01.875 --> 09:04.943
[indistinct chatter]

09:10.584 --> 09:12.217
Aunt Sadie!

09:12.219 --> 09:15.020
Nicky!

09:15.022 --> 09:16.621
-Hi! -Hi!

09:16.623 --> 09:19.991
[laughs] Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

09:19.993 --> 09:22.160
-Oh! What are you doing here? -Oh, my God.

09:22.162 --> 09:25.263
I had to come see my favorite little niece.

09:25.265 --> 09:28.333
-I'm your only niece. -Ooh, that's right.

09:28.335 --> 09:31.036
-Ooh. -Ooh. Oh, you're so gorgeous.

09:31.038 --> 09:33.905
-[Sadie] Don't you know? -Sadie.

09:33.907 --> 09:38.109
Hi, Chloe. Come on, don't be sad.

09:38.111 --> 09:40.011
I should be incredibly mad at you.

09:40.013 --> 09:42.180
One whole year and nothing?

09:42.182 --> 09:45.050
[Sadie] Uh, yeah, but I'm sorry.

09:45.052 --> 09:46.585
[Chloe] Mm... [Sadie] Ping, ping, ping, ping.

09:46.587 --> 09:49.955
-Well, I'm not even mad. -Yeah, don't be.

09:49.957 --> 09:53.325
Hi! Hi!

09:53.327 --> 09:56.728
[Nicole] Look. [Sadie] Wow! Ha-ha-ha!

09:56.730 --> 09:58.229
[Nicole laughs]

09:58.231 --> 10:01.666
[Sadie] Oh, my God! [Nicole] Heh-heh.

10:01.668 --> 10:04.035
[Chloe] So what do you think? Does the house feel smaller?

10:04.037 --> 10:07.839
[Sadie] No, it's the same. I mean, it feels kind of big.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.908
[Nicole grunts]

10:09.910 --> 10:11.910
-Oh, wait, here. -No, no, no, no. No, no, no, no.

10:11.912 --> 10:13.311
-I've got it. -Okay. Um...

10:13.313 --> 10:16.047
-Are you in my old room still? -[chuckles]

10:16.049 --> 10:17.716
-Yeah, best room in the house. -Okay.

10:17.718 --> 10:19.317
Well, will you put my stuff in there, then?

10:19.319 --> 10:22.053
-[Nicole] Yes, master. -We have a spare room.

10:22.055 --> 10:25.190
-Don't you want your own space? -No! I wanna be with Nicky.

10:25.192 --> 10:28.259
[gasps] Oh, yay!

10:28.261 --> 10:31.329
[instrumental music]

10:35.035 --> 10:37.936
I am home.

10:37.938 --> 10:40.772
Oh, it's been a long time since I've been able to say that.

10:44.211 --> 10:45.777
I really love your hair, by the way.

10:45.779 --> 10:48.013
-Really? -Yeah.

10:48.015 --> 10:50.081
You haven't grown it out since you were little.

10:52.019 --> 10:54.085
I'm glad you like it.

10:57.090 --> 10:59.257
Where were you?

10:59.259 --> 11:03.862
I think the last I heard was, um... New Orleans?

11:05.932 --> 11:08.967
Yeah. Doesn't really matter.

11:10.404 --> 11:12.837
It matters to me.

11:12.839 --> 11:14.806
[footsteps approaching]

11:14.808 --> 11:17.742
How long are you here for?

11:17.744 --> 11:20.378
I don't know. How long will you have me?

11:20.380 --> 11:23.014
Well, for as long as you'd like.

11:23.016 --> 11:26.217
I mean, it's still your home, too.

11:26.219 --> 11:30.121
-[Nicole] Move in! Move in! -Okay.

11:30.123 --> 11:32.090
I mean, I don't have anywhere I've gotta go.

11:32.092 --> 11:35.126
So I guess we could just take it, like, one day at a time,

11:35.128 --> 11:36.761
if that works for you.

11:38.198 --> 11:39.864
You'd probably be sick of me by tomorrow.

11:39.866 --> 11:40.899
-No way. -Really?

11:40.901 --> 11:42.233
'Cause I'll keep doin' this.

11:42.235 --> 11:43.968
I would love it.

11:43.970 --> 11:45.236
[crickets chirping]

11:45.238 --> 11:47.172
[Nicole] Well, why did you leave us?

11:47.174 --> 11:50.141
I, um...

11:50.143 --> 11:52.444
Well, you know, your mom had been

11:52.446 --> 11:55.146
basically looking after me since she was 15.

11:55.148 --> 11:58.483
-No, that's, that's not-- -No, it is true. Totally true.

11:58.485 --> 12:01.753
'Cause after my mom and our dad died,

12:01.755 --> 12:03.988
Aunt Betty moved in.

12:03.990 --> 12:06.257
And she just... She sucked.

12:06.259 --> 12:08.827
She just, like, drank G and Ts

12:08.829 --> 12:11.796
and watched Bold And The Beautiful all day, every day.

12:11.798 --> 12:15.500
So your mom was basically all I had.

12:15.502 --> 12:18.002
And then she had you when she was a baby.

12:18.004 --> 12:20.405
That was, that was great and fine and--

12:20.407 --> 12:23.875
-So it was my fault you left. -No! It wasn't... It's not.

12:23.877 --> 12:26.177
Not... That's not true. Um, that's not what I meant.

12:26.179 --> 12:27.779
I just like...

12:28.315 --> 12:30.782
It was just...

12:30.784 --> 12:35.053
I had more energy than this town could handle.

12:37.891 --> 12:41.793
So what did this girl do, the one that you hit?

12:41.795 --> 12:43.194
[chuckles softly]

12:43.196 --> 12:45.964
-Bitch was about to talk shit. -Hey--

12:45.966 --> 12:49.934
Wait, she was about to talk shit. So she hadn't?

12:49.936 --> 12:52.103
Oh, so you're just nippin' it in the bud, are you?

12:52.105 --> 12:53.371
-Mm-hmm. -[Chloe] Be careful.

12:53.373 --> 12:56.508
-This one's impulsive. -Oh-oh.

12:56.510 --> 12:59.310
Like me.

12:59.312 --> 13:02.547
I always said Nicky and I are kindred spirits.

13:04.451 --> 13:06.518
[crickets chirping]

13:08.088 --> 13:11.156
[instrumental music]

13:14.060 --> 13:16.094
[Nicole] I know I should have outgrown this thing by now,

13:16.096 --> 13:18.496
but I just...

13:18.498 --> 13:21.065
I just love it.

13:21.067 --> 13:23.434
I think we'd all be better off if we never outgrew the things

13:23.436 --> 13:25.336
we loved as kids.

13:28.208 --> 13:30.508
It's so funny that you still have that.

13:30.510 --> 13:33.211
I'd be roadkill if it wasn't for you.

13:34.181 --> 13:37.048
I owe you my life, Aunt Sadie.

13:37.050 --> 13:39.384
Mm, you owe your life to your mom.

13:39.386 --> 13:43.521
Mm, yeah. She reminds me of it every day.

13:43.523 --> 13:45.990
Your mom is the strongest person I know.

13:45.992 --> 13:47.192
You'd be surprised what can happen

13:47.194 --> 13:49.093
if you just open up to her.

13:49.095 --> 13:52.831
-She doesn't give me a chance. -What do you mean?

13:55.836 --> 13:58.570
-I sort of have a boyfriend now. -Whoo-hoo!

13:58.572 --> 14:02.273
[laughs] Nicky... Wait, what's his name?

14:02.275 --> 14:06.411
-His name is Derek. -Derek.

14:06.413 --> 14:10.048
Derek and Nicole. Nicole and Derek.

14:10.050 --> 14:11.916
I love it. What else?

14:11.918 --> 14:16.554
He is cute and...

14:18.091 --> 14:20.491
I don't know, he likes video games.

14:20.493 --> 14:24.362
-He sounds perfect. So... -[chuckles]

14:24.364 --> 14:27.398
He's better than that. I don't know.

14:27.400 --> 14:29.400
The other day...

14:30.937 --> 14:34.639
mom walked in on us and our shirts were off.

14:34.641 --> 14:37.208
[gasps] Nicky!

14:37.210 --> 14:39.444
-Are you sleeping with him? -No! No, no, no.

14:39.446 --> 14:41.946
No, no, no. We were just messing around.

14:41.948 --> 14:45.450
But, see, at least you ask,

14:45.452 --> 14:47.919
instead of just assuming.

14:47.921 --> 14:50.121
Have you slept with anyone?

14:51.324 --> 14:53.958
No! That's a good thing.

14:53.960 --> 14:56.594
Teenage boys have a lot to learn.

14:56.596 --> 14:59.297
It's really nice to be able to talk to you about this stuff.

14:59.299 --> 15:03.101
With my mom, it's just so weird.

15:03.103 --> 15:06.504
"Nicole, are you using protection?"

15:06.506 --> 15:09.007
Yeah, well, imagine if you had a baby right now.

15:09.009 --> 15:11.476
Yeah. No, thank you.

15:11.478 --> 15:14.679
She had to raise you all on her own.

15:14.681 --> 15:18.683
She's had to do everything on her own. So, I don't know.

15:18.685 --> 15:20.652
I guess it seems like she's kinda hard on you,

15:20.654 --> 15:23.521
but you can always talk to her.

15:24.491 --> 15:25.957
Always.

15:31.031 --> 15:33.364
Mm, whoo.

15:33.366 --> 15:35.300
[chuckles] I like that haircut of you, though.

15:35.302 --> 15:37.702
-[chuckles] -[Sadie] It looks great.

15:37.704 --> 15:39.537
You're not mad at me for copying you?

15:39.539 --> 15:41.940
I mean, you didn't really copy me.

15:41.942 --> 15:44.342
Uh, yes, I did.

15:46.012 --> 15:49.080
[instrumental music]

15:51.084 --> 15:52.984
Ugh!

15:52.986 --> 15:55.687
-[chuckles] You look pretty. -That is...

15:55.689 --> 15:59.324
-Yeah. -Mom says I kinda look like you.

16:01.094 --> 16:03.194
Yeah, sure!

16:17.344 --> 16:20.411
[eerie music]

16:24.250 --> 16:27.318
[Young Nicole laughing]

16:31.224 --> 16:34.092
[Young Nicole] I owe you my life, Aunt Sadie.

16:47.140 --> 16:49.407
-Good morning. -Good morning.

16:49.409 --> 16:52.477
[cutlery clattering]

17:00.086 --> 17:03.021
-Hey, Sadie. -Mm?

17:04.391 --> 17:06.590
-Can-can we talk for a minute? -Yeah.

17:15.367 --> 17:19.569
-Is everything okay? -What do you mean?

17:19.571 --> 17:24.075
Oh, well, I mean, you showed up out of the blue...

17:24.077 --> 17:27.712
which, don't get me wrong, I'm grateful for.

17:28.515 --> 17:30.581
I'm thrilled to see you.

17:34.354 --> 17:37.388
But if it's because...

17:37.390 --> 17:39.424
you need help with something

17:39.426 --> 17:42.593
or somebody or anything...

17:45.598 --> 17:47.598
you need to tell me.

17:52.505 --> 17:54.172
-Sadie. -Yeah.

17:54.174 --> 17:56.407
No, sorry, I'm just, uh...

17:58.311 --> 18:00.645
I, um ...

18:03.683 --> 18:07.285
I wanted to come home 'cause like...

18:08.521 --> 18:10.655
I've kind of...

18:14.861 --> 18:17.595
you know, made a mess of a lot of things

18:17.597 --> 18:21.499
and... I've, like, failed in literally everything

18:21.501 --> 18:25.303
I've tried to do, so, I, uh...

18:28.274 --> 18:30.241
I don't have many options.

18:30.243 --> 18:32.376
I just thought that I should, you know, come home

18:32.378 --> 18:36.414
and... um, maybe start over?

18:36.416 --> 18:39.784
It's, which is probably stupid.

18:39.786 --> 18:43.254
No. It doesn't sound stupid to me at all.

18:46.392 --> 18:48.593
Hey, look, I-I don't, I don't know

18:48.595 --> 18:50.728
what you've been going through, but...

18:52.565 --> 18:54.565
I know that you're still young

18:54.567 --> 18:56.667
and, I think,

18:56.669 --> 18:59.704
maybe you're being too hard on yourself.

18:59.706 --> 19:01.272
And I think it makes perfect sense

19:01.274 --> 19:04.408
to take a moment, regroup, rebuild.

19:05.778 --> 19:08.546
And in the meantime, you're home. Right?

19:08.548 --> 19:10.281
Mm-hmm.

19:11.584 --> 19:14.752
Come here. No more sad face. Give me a hug.

19:17.157 --> 19:20.224
[Chloe humming]

19:27.634 --> 19:29.700
[Nicole] What's going on in here?

19:29.702 --> 19:31.502
[Sadie] Nothing.

19:33.206 --> 19:35.439
I was just getting ready for work.

19:35.441 --> 19:36.741
Mm-hmm.

19:38.411 --> 19:40.178
Oh, and, Sadie,

19:40.180 --> 19:42.747
I'm not exactly thrilled with the idea

19:42.749 --> 19:46.751
of Nicole having too much fun as she's suspended.

19:46.753 --> 19:50.888
Oh, okay. Should we make her scrub the floors, then?

19:50.890 --> 19:53.758
You know, that might teach her a lesson.

19:55.662 --> 19:58.829
But I know she hasn't seen her Aunt Sadie in a long time, so...

19:58.831 --> 20:01.933
And that girl was gonna talk shit.

20:01.935 --> 20:04.202
-That is true. -All right.

20:04.204 --> 20:07.838
Let's not go there now, but I suppose

20:07.840 --> 20:11.475
I can postpone the punishment for now.

20:11.477 --> 20:13.578
-Thank you! -Aw...

20:13.580 --> 20:15.346
-All right, have fun. -Yup.

20:15.348 --> 20:16.914
Still be good, but don't have too much fun.

20:16.916 --> 20:20.351
Nope. Never when you're not here.

20:20.353 --> 20:22.553
[Russian accent] Eh, so what should we do first

20:22.555 --> 20:24.255
as good girls?

20:24.257 --> 20:26.757
[Russian accent] We do, uh... garage?

20:26.759 --> 20:29.927
-[gasps] Okay, you weirdo. -Okay.

20:29.929 --> 20:31.996
[Sadie chuckles]

20:35.702 --> 20:37.835
-Okay. -Yeah?

20:40.240 --> 20:43.808
¶ Ta ta-da-da ¶

20:43.810 --> 20:46.544
Oh, my... Hey, did...

20:46.546 --> 20:49.614
-I smashed this to pieces! -I know.

20:49.616 --> 20:52.383
One of your famous temper tantrums.

20:52.385 --> 20:56.654
Mom told me all about it. I get them, too.

20:56.656 --> 21:00.024
It took me forever to put it back together.

21:00.026 --> 21:02.860
-Look. -Yeah, it's the Edwards family.

21:02.862 --> 21:04.695
-I made these guys. -[chuckles]

21:04.697 --> 21:06.397
I used to play with them all the time.

21:06.399 --> 21:08.032
-Wait, you did? -[Nicole] Yeah.

21:08.034 --> 21:12.870
I also, uh, have that book that you wrote about them.

21:15.541 --> 21:17.875
-You're such a good writer. -Mm-hmm.

21:17.877 --> 21:21.279
Shay and I added a few of our own, but they probably suck.

21:21.281 --> 21:22.546
[Sadie chuckles]

21:24.017 --> 21:26.684
[instrumental music]

21:27.920 --> 21:30.521
We used to get dressed up

21:30.523 --> 21:33.291
and pretend we were the Edward sisters.

21:33.293 --> 21:36.360
[indistinct whispering]

21:37.430 --> 21:40.431
[Sadie] So nobody understood...

21:42.969 --> 21:44.769
Nobody understood.

21:44.771 --> 21:47.972
Are you... mad?

21:47.974 --> 21:50.041
No.

21:50.043 --> 21:52.710
[chuckles] Kinda seems like you're mad.

21:52.712 --> 21:56.480
No, I'm really not. It's just a lot of nostalgia.

21:56.482 --> 21:59.617
Haven't looked at this stuff in ages.

21:59.619 --> 22:03.087
Hey, are nana's old theater costumes down here still?

22:03.089 --> 22:04.322
Mm-hmm.

22:04.324 --> 22:07.391
[instrumental music]

22:21.574 --> 22:25.343
[laughing] Come and get me!

22:26.946 --> 22:30.014
[intense music]

22:30.683 --> 22:32.583
[giggling]

22:32.585 --> 22:36.654
[singsong] Good day! My lady.

22:37.590 --> 22:40.057
[engines revving]

22:40.893 --> 22:42.760
Kill her...

22:44.464 --> 22:45.830
Sadie?

22:47.767 --> 22:49.600
What's wrong?

22:49.602 --> 22:52.103
Come on, we should go.

22:52.105 --> 22:53.971
We don't wanna get caught playin' hooky.

22:53.973 --> 22:56.040
Mom won't like that.

23:00.413 --> 23:02.880
Bet you can't catch me! Ha-ha!

23:02.882 --> 23:05.116
-Yes, I can! -Bet you can't!

23:05.118 --> 23:07.785
[instrumental music]

23:08.955 --> 23:11.989
-[Sadie] Ah! -[Nicole chuckles]

23:21.501 --> 23:24.001
-[Sadie screaming] -[Nicole screaming]

23:24.003 --> 23:26.570
Ooh!

23:26.572 --> 23:30.474
-How did you do that? -I'm very, very, well, smart.

23:30.476 --> 23:33.411
[indistinct chatter]

23:42.088 --> 23:43.621
[car lock beeps]

23:45.892 --> 23:49.193
[Shay] Thanks. See you. [Alex] Okay. See you.

23:49.195 --> 23:52.430
-Well, hello, Shay. -Hey, Chloe.

23:52.432 --> 23:55.132
Did my dear darling daughter ask you over?

23:55.134 --> 23:57.902
-Yeah. -Is that okay?

23:57.904 --> 23:59.904
-Hello, Alex. How are you? -Hello, Chloe.

23:59.906 --> 24:01.705
It's nice to see you again.

24:01.707 --> 24:05.709
Did Shay here tell you that Nicole was suspended yesterday?

24:05.711 --> 24:07.578
[chuckles] Uh, no.

24:07.580 --> 24:08.746
-She didn't mention that. -[Nicole and Sadie screaming]

24:08.748 --> 24:11.449
-Mm... -Come real quick.

24:11.451 --> 24:13.484
Sounds like you're not supposed to be here, sweetie.

24:13.486 --> 24:16.220
-Dad. -No, actually, it's okay.

24:16.222 --> 24:18.823
Sadie is back in town, and, uh,

24:18.825 --> 24:20.758
well, I might've postponed the punishment.

24:20.760 --> 24:22.693
So go ahead. You're good.

24:24.864 --> 24:26.230
-Sadie, huh? -Yeah.

24:26.232 --> 24:28.766
-Blast from the past. -You're telling me.

24:28.768 --> 24:30.734
Shay mentioned that there might be a party tonight.

24:30.736 --> 24:35.072
I was thinkin' if the kids went, we could, um, get together.

24:37.577 --> 24:39.643
Well, if they go,

24:39.645 --> 24:41.645
I'll probably just be hangin' out with my sister.

24:41.647 --> 24:44.014
-Okay. -But I'll catch you next time.

24:44.016 --> 24:45.483
Okay.

24:47.820 --> 24:49.520
[Shay] Hey, what are you guys doing?

24:49.522 --> 24:50.955
[Nicole] Hey, Sadie, what should Shay be?

24:50.957 --> 24:52.623
-Hey. -I can't believe you're here.

24:52.625 --> 24:56.260
Mm-hmm. Hey, look at you. You're all grown up.

24:56.262 --> 24:57.928
How's your family?

24:57.930 --> 24:59.663
-Remember my brother, Rory? -Mm-hmm.

24:59.665 --> 25:00.931
He's pre-med at Columbia.

25:00.933 --> 25:02.733
-Oh, wow! -Go, Rory.

25:02.735 --> 25:04.502
-Pretty, yeah. -Nice.

25:04.504 --> 25:07.571
-What about your parents? -Oh, uh...

25:07.573 --> 25:10.140
They're separated. Her mom kinda bailed.

25:10.142 --> 25:12.209
Oh, no. I'm so sorry.

25:12.211 --> 25:14.044
-They'll get back together. -Mm.

25:14.046 --> 25:15.713
They're a total mess without each other.

25:15.715 --> 25:17.882
Yeah, I'm-I'm sure that's what's gonna happen.

25:17.884 --> 25:19.884
But Nicole's right, we have to get you changed.

25:19.886 --> 25:22.553
-You look ridiculous. -Yeah, what is this?

25:25.157 --> 25:26.690
[Nicole] Hey, mom.

25:26.692 --> 25:28.559
There's a party at Kenny Killian's tonight.

25:28.561 --> 25:30.561
Can we go?

25:30.563 --> 25:33.797
I feel like this, absolutely, should be out of the question.

25:33.799 --> 25:37.735
Oh, please, oh, fair noble queen!

25:37.737 --> 25:40.070
You may taketh my head on the morrow,

25:40.072 --> 25:44.275
but tonight let me partake in the revelry.

25:44.277 --> 25:47.545
-[chuckles] -Oh, come on, please!

25:47.547 --> 25:48.846
I don't know, I feel like Sadie

25:48.848 --> 25:50.281
doesn't wanna go to a high-school party.

25:50.283 --> 25:52.783
No, I don't mind chaperoning these butt-heads.

25:52.785 --> 25:56.287
But we go under one condition. We go in costume.

25:56.289 --> 25:58.656
-[laughs] -Yeah?

25:58.658 --> 26:01.225
-That's hilarious. -I don't know.

26:01.227 --> 26:03.794
-[clucking] -Come on!

26:03.796 --> 26:05.930
Get you changed, anyway.

26:06.866 --> 26:09.333
Looks like you two had fun.

26:09.335 --> 26:12.937
Yeah, we did. Nicole feels like a little sister to me.

26:12.939 --> 26:16.941
So... does she confide in you?

26:16.943 --> 26:18.576
-Don't... -Do what?

26:18.578 --> 26:21.178
Don't turn me into an informant, Chloe.

26:21.981 --> 26:23.347
I'm not.

26:24.884 --> 26:27.351
I would just say...

26:27.353 --> 26:29.219
don't assume things

26:29.221 --> 26:33.190
'cause... she's a good girl.

26:35.695 --> 26:36.961
Okay?

26:37.964 --> 26:39.229
You look pretty.

26:40.967 --> 26:42.366
[Nicole] I feel like we shouldn't have brought you here,

26:42.368 --> 26:43.867
you know?

26:45.071 --> 26:48.038
[Sadie] Yeah, you should have.

26:48.040 --> 26:49.873
I don't know what we were thinking.

26:49.875 --> 26:52.343
-I can't go in like this. -Yes, you can.

26:52.345 --> 26:54.211
You can do literally whatever you want in high school

26:54.213 --> 26:57.214
as long as you have one thing, confidence.

26:57.216 --> 26:58.882
[sighs]

26:58.884 --> 27:01.185
Shay! Shay! Shay! Shay!

27:01.187 --> 27:04.822
-[both] Shay! Shay! Shay! Shay! -Oh! Oh, my God!

27:04.824 --> 27:07.391
[door creaking]

27:07.393 --> 27:10.661
[instrumental music]

27:19.639 --> 27:22.706
[indistinct chatter]

27:37.790 --> 27:40.090
[laughter]

27:40.092 --> 27:41.792
Crazy.

27:49.702 --> 27:53.270
-Come on in. -Let's go out.

27:53.272 --> 27:56.740
Get a bite to eat. It'll be like a proper date.

27:56.742 --> 27:59.376
Mm, my feet hurt.

27:59.378 --> 28:01.078
Come on, let's just order in

28:01.080 --> 28:03.814
and that way we can fuck while we wait.

28:03.816 --> 28:07.718
-[chuckles] Don't do that. -Do what?

28:07.720 --> 28:09.086
Try to distract me from the fact

28:09.088 --> 28:11.755
that you don't wanna be seen with me.

28:11.757 --> 28:13.757
-Ever. -Aw...

28:13.759 --> 28:16.193
-Look, it's just-- -Come on in. Okay?

28:16.195 --> 28:19.063
And you're cute when you pout.

28:19.065 --> 28:20.464
[indistinct chatter]

28:20.466 --> 28:22.066
-Good one! -[laughter]

28:22.068 --> 28:24.034
-Nicole? -Derek!

28:24.036 --> 28:27.838
-What are you doin' here? -What am I doing here?

28:27.840 --> 28:30.107
-This is my Aunt Sadie. -[Derek] Oh!

28:30.109 --> 28:33.010
-I-I heard a lot about you. -Oh, yeah?

28:33.012 --> 28:34.411
What have you heard?

28:34.413 --> 28:36.280
Um, I heard you saved

28:36.282 --> 28:37.948
my girlfriend's life when she was little.

28:37.950 --> 28:40.284
Did he just say the G word?

28:40.286 --> 28:44.421
Well, you take care of this one. She's literally the best.

28:44.423 --> 28:47.024
I got my eye on you.

28:47.860 --> 28:50.160
Cheers to that, I guess.

28:52.031 --> 28:54.465
-Will you be a doll? -Yeah.

28:54.467 --> 28:56.400
[indistinct chatter]

28:56.402 --> 28:59.069
Nicky, he's hot! [burps]

28:59.071 --> 29:01.872
I'm just happy she's back.

29:01.874 --> 29:05.042
And it could be good for Nicole, too.

29:05.044 --> 29:08.011
And when are we gonna tell her and Shay about us?

29:09.448 --> 29:12.916
Well, w-what is it that we should be telling exactly?

29:12.918 --> 29:15.853
The truth, that we like spending time together

29:15.855 --> 29:19.156
and-and maybe that'll become something in the future

29:19.158 --> 29:22.893
or maybe it won't, but right now something is happening.

29:22.895 --> 29:26.230
Mm... not yet.

29:26.232 --> 29:29.066
Give Nicole some credit. She can take it.

29:29.068 --> 29:33.437
Sometimes I think that you're trying to keep her a kid.

29:33.439 --> 29:36.240
I'm not trying to prevent her from growing up.

29:36.242 --> 29:38.408
I'm doing the exact opposite.

29:39.111 --> 29:40.410
Okay.

29:42.047 --> 29:46.083
Look, they're gonna be adults in a hot minute,

29:46.085 --> 29:48.218
which means we'll have plenty of time to figure out

29:48.220 --> 29:50.320
what to do with ourselves.

29:55.227 --> 29:57.261
Okay.

29:57.263 --> 30:00.330
[cheering]

30:01.801 --> 30:04.868
[party music]

30:14.346 --> 30:16.346
[Sadie] Whoo-hoo!

30:32.364 --> 30:35.132
-I thought you would want this. -Huh?

30:35.134 --> 30:36.600
I-I thought you would want this.

30:36.602 --> 30:40.604
Oh, yeah! You're totally right. Cheers.

30:41.841 --> 30:44.441
-I'm Sadie. Who are you? -Kenny.

30:44.443 --> 30:46.844
Oh, you're Kenny! This is your party!

30:46.846 --> 30:50.147
-Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm. -Oh, cool!

30:50.149 --> 30:51.615
I like your mask.

30:51.617 --> 30:54.318
It's cool that you guys, you know, do your own thing.

30:54.320 --> 30:57.988
Yeah, I mean, we like to play.

30:59.925 --> 31:02.526
Where do you go to school?

31:02.528 --> 31:04.628
A-are you a senior?

31:04.630 --> 31:07.231
-Yeah. -Okay.

31:07.233 --> 31:09.867
Yeah. Um...

31:09.869 --> 31:11.635
I'm homeschooled.

31:11.637 --> 31:16.206
But... it's my last year before college.

31:16.208 --> 31:18.342
-Yeah. -Where do you wanna go?

31:18.344 --> 31:21.511
-Columbia. Pre-med. -Oh.

31:21.513 --> 31:25.115
Wow! Beauty and brains.

31:25.117 --> 31:26.884
-Where have you been hiding, S-- -Kenny!

31:26.886 --> 31:28.652
Nah, it's okay.

31:28.654 --> 31:31.421
I have been in hiding.

31:31.423 --> 31:35.025
But now that you've found me...

31:35.027 --> 31:37.394
what are you gonna do about it?

31:39.098 --> 31:40.664
Want to see my room?

31:42.167 --> 31:44.434
-Yeah. -Okay.

31:44.436 --> 31:46.336
[crowd cheering]

31:46.338 --> 31:48.939
-Wow! -Oh, yeah!

31:50.175 --> 31:52.276
What's her deal?

31:54.013 --> 31:55.412
Like, how do you mean?

31:55.414 --> 31:58.115
I mean, can you imagine ever wanting to go

31:58.117 --> 32:00.484
to a high-school party again? Because I can't.

32:00.486 --> 32:04.521
[chuckles] You know, she said she wanted to start over.

32:04.523 --> 32:07.157
That's one way to go about it.

32:07.159 --> 32:08.425
[chuckles]

32:10.296 --> 32:12.963
She's always been a little...

32:12.965 --> 32:13.997
immature.

32:13.999 --> 32:15.933
[Alex] How old is she?

32:15.935 --> 32:17.467
[Chloe] She's 25.

32:18.671 --> 32:20.404
[chuckles]

32:21.540 --> 32:24.074
-Do you wanna sit down? -Oh, yeah, sure.

32:25.945 --> 32:29.012
[party music]

32:57.409 --> 32:59.543
Take off your mask.

33:00.479 --> 33:02.045
How come?

33:03.716 --> 33:06.984
[music continues]

33:12.992 --> 33:15.759
I think I really like you, Kenny.

33:31.610 --> 33:33.643
Kenny.

33:33.645 --> 33:36.480
-What? -I have to go.

33:37.182 --> 33:38.648
Why is that?

33:40.219 --> 33:43.720
My mom is really strict.

33:45.024 --> 33:48.725
-Well, that sucks. -No, it doesn't.

33:48.727 --> 33:51.795
It means she really cares about me.

33:53.065 --> 33:56.533
She's giving me a test tomorrow.

33:56.535 --> 33:58.435
-Because I'm homeschooled. -Oh, yeah, right.

33:58.437 --> 34:00.737
-Remember? -Right.

34:07.212 --> 34:08.678
Bye.

34:14.620 --> 34:16.686
How do I look?

34:17.656 --> 34:19.723
-You look amazing! -Really?

34:19.725 --> 34:22.225
Yeah! Oh, my God!

34:22.226 --> 34:24.460
-Did you do a streak? -Yeah, I did. But don't worry.

34:24.463 --> 34:26.563
This is, like, not my actual hair. I didn't cut it again.

34:26.565 --> 34:28.364
-This is one of nana's wigs. -Okay.

34:28.367 --> 34:31.234
I was, like, chopping it up all last night while you snored.

34:31.235 --> 34:33.703
-I don't snore. -You... Yes, you do!

34:33.705 --> 34:36.572
-I snore? -Yeah. It's cute, though.

34:36.574 --> 34:38.275
It looks good.

34:39.110 --> 34:41.210
-Twins! -Twin...

34:41.213 --> 34:42.712
Hey, did you know that last night, like,

34:42.714 --> 34:45.148
half the party thought that you were our age?

34:45.150 --> 34:46.483
-Really? -Yeah!

34:46.485 --> 34:48.485
-That's stupid. -[chuckles]

34:48.487 --> 34:50.286
My Aunt Sadie's still got it.

34:50.289 --> 34:53.690
[chuckles] Oh, you're boney!

34:53.692 --> 34:57.694
Well, that's why I have my healthy breakfast.

